io.sphere.sdk.products

Interface ProductProjection

  • All Superinterfaces:
    CreationTimestamped, Identifiable<Product>, ProductIdentifiable, ProductLike<ProductProjection,Product>, Referenceable<Product>, ResourceIdentifiable<Product>, ResourceView<ProductProjection,Product>, Timestamped, Versioned<Product>, WithKey

    public interface ProductProjection
extends ProductLike<ProductProjection,Product>, Referenceable<Product>, Versioned<Product>
    A projected representation of a product shows the product with its current or staged data. ProductProjections are views of Products.

    To create, update or delete ProductProjections you have to use the Product lifecycle classes.

    Operations:

    • Fetch by ID with ProductProjectionByIdGet
    If you need ProductProjection for a method but you have a product, you can transform a product into a product projection: 
    final Product product = getProduct();

final ProductProjection staged = product.toProjection(ProductProjectionType.STAGED);

assertThat(staged).overridingErrorMessage("staged is always present").isNotNull();
assertThat(staged.getName()).isEqualTo(product.getMasterData().getStaged().getName());

final ProductProjection current = product.toProjection(ProductProjectionType.CURRENT);
assertThat(current).overridingErrorMessage("current can be empty").isNull();

    See the test code.
    toReference() returns not are reference to a ProductProjection but to a Product.
